{{der-top|Compounds}}
* {{ja-r|月桃|げっとう}}: [[shell ginger]]
* {{ja-r|桃花|とうか}}: [[peach]] [[blossom]] [[flower]]
* {{ja-r|桃果|とうか}}: peach ([[fruit]])
* {{ja-r|桃矢|^とうや}}: “peach arrow” → a male given name
{{der-bottom}}

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|桃色|ももいろ}}: pink
* {{ja-r|桃色 鸚哥|ももいろ いんこ}}: “pink parakeet” → {{taxlink|Eolophus roseicapillus|species|noshow=1}}: [[galah]], {{vern|rose-breasted cockatoo}}
* {{ja-r|桃色 遊戯|ももいろ ゆうぎ}}: “pink playing” → sex play
* {{ja-r|桃%尻|もも%じり}}: “peach butt” → from the way that the end of a peach is often pointy, and thus difficult to place stably: somebody who is bad at horse-riding; a fidgety, restless person
* {{ja-r|桃%園|もも%ぞの}}: a peach orchard
* {{ja-r|桃 割れ|もも われ}}: “split peach” → a hairstyle of Meiji and Taisho era, featuring a bun resembling a halved peach
{{der-bottom}}

{{der-top|Idioms}}
* {{ja-r|桃 栗 三 年 柿 八 年|もも くり さん ねん かき はち ねん}}: “peach and chestnut take three years [to bear fruit], persimmons take eight” → it often takes time to bear the fruit of one's actions
{{der-bottom}}
